---
import { withBase } from '../utils/paths';
import LegalLayout from '../components/legal/LegalLayout.astro';
import LegalSection from '../components/legal/LegalSection.astro';
---

<LegalLayout
  title="Draft License Terms | PrintKeep by BMR"
  description="Preliminary license terms placeholder for PrintKeep by BMR while the final software license, catalog model, and distribution terms remain undecided."
  eyebrow="Draft license terms"
  heading="Preliminary license placeholder for future app distribution."
  intro="This page records the current license-term status without selecting final desktop app, catalog, or commercial terms."
  currentPath="/license-terms/"
>
  <LegalSection title="No final app license selected">
    <p>
      No final software license for the PrintKeep by BMR desktop app is selected in this website repository. This page is a
      preliminary placeholder and should not be treated as an open-source license, proprietary license, end-user license
      agreement, catalog license, entitlement policy, or commercial purchase agreement.
    </p>
  </LegalSection>

  <LegalSection title="Planned model under consideration">
    <p>
      The current product direction includes a planned free desktop Core focused on printer profiles, maintenance tasks,
      history, parts, incidents, and local backup. Optional paid verified catalogs, license keys, entitlements, and device
      activation are future commercial planning topics and are not final terms.
    </p>
    <p>
      If future account claim or recovery workflows are introduced, license terms and privacy notices should explain what
      account data, recovery data, device data, and entitlement records are used. If an Early Supporter program is later
      launched, any Founder licenses would need reviewed terms before purchase or activation and should remain conditional
      until final reward definitions are published.
    </p>
  </LegalSection>

  <LegalSection title="Repository and website status">
    <p>
      The website repository is marked private in its package metadata and does not include a dedicated license file at
      this stage. Future project owners should decide and document whether website code, app code, documentation, catalog
      content, and brand assets have separate licensing rules.
    </p>
  </LegalSection>

  <LegalSection title="Future desktop app and catalog distribution">
    <p>
      Before any desktop installer, binary, package, app store listing, private beta build, paid catalog, license key, or
      entitlement workflow is distributed, the project should publish reviewed license terms that explain permitted use,
      restrictions, updates, support expectations, warranty limitations, activation rules, catalog access, and termination
      rules if applicable.
    </p>
  </LegalSection>

  <LegalSection title="Third-party dependencies">
    <p>
      PrintKeep by BMR may rely on third-party dependencies for the website, desktop app, packaging, catalogs, or
      documentation. Those dependencies can have their own licenses and notices. A future release should include a
      dependency notice process and any required attributions before distribution.
    </p>
  </LegalSection>

  <LegalSection title="Commercial model not final here">
    <p>
      This placeholder does not announce final paid plans, subscriptions, purchases, commercial licensing, app store
      distribution, public availability, catalog pricing, license duration, update periods, activation limits, or Founder
      license rights. Release status remains described on the <a href={withBase('/download/')}>release preparation page</a>,
      with broader sequencing on the <a href={withBase('/roadmap/')}>roadmap</a> and catalog planning on the
      <a href={withBase('/catalogs/')}>catalogs page</a>.
    </p>
  </LegalSection>
</LegalLayout>
